Dan IS BACK IN THE U.K.             AND ON TRACK.

Celebrated yesterday, Sunday 16th September, twenty seventh anniversary of The Terry Fox run.
Visit this meaningful monument to him, just east of Thunder Bay Ontario Canada. Terry started his cross country run from St. Johns Newfoundland in 1980. His cancer worsened  and he had to give up his attempt as he was so sick.
OUR OWN CANADIAN HERO.
What else did CANADA give the world?

So we are still waiting for December Boys to begin up here in the Canada. My last check revealed that tribute.com and the cineplex site are at least on the same page now, Oct 12th.
